{"questionId":"9084658","questionHtml":"<p>A sample of a gas has volume <em><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>V</mi></math></em> and contains <em><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>N</mi></math></em> molecules, each of mass <em><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>m</mi></math></em>. The average translational speed of the molecules is <em><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>u</mi></math></em>.</p>\n<p>Which expression is equivalent to the pressure of the gas?</p>\n<p><br>A.&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>3</mn></mfrac><mfrac><mrow><mi>N</mi><mi>V</mi></mrow><mi>m</mi></mfrac><msup><mi>u</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></math></p>\n<p>B.&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>3</mn></mfrac><mfrac><mrow><mi>N</mi><mi>m</mi></mrow><mi>V</mi></mfrac><msup><mi>u</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></math></p>\n<p>C.&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>3</mn></mfrac><mfrac><mi>N</mi><mrow><mi>m</mi><mi>V</mi></mrow></mfrac><msup><mi>u</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></math></p>\n<p>D.&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>3</mn></mfrac><mfrac><mi>m</mi><mrow><mi>N</mi><mi>V</mi></mrow></mfrac><msup><mi>u</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></math></p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>B</p>","meta":{"questionId":"9084658","referenceCode":"EXE.1A.SL.TZ0.10","subjectId":"59-dp-physics-first-assessment-2025","title":"A sample of a gas has volume V and contains N molecules, each of mass m. The average translational speed of the molecules is u. Which expression is equivalent to the pressure of th","paper":"1A","level":"SL","questionNumber":"10","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["B. The particulate nature of matter","B. The particulate nature of matter","B.3 Gas laws"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}